06/09/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- A delegation from the NATO Parliamentary Assembly is expected to arrive on an annual working visit Monday (6 September). 
The delegation will meet with representatives from the interior, foreign and defence ministries for talks on a range of issues.
Also Monday, the foreign ministry confirmed that a nine-year-old Turkish girl died during the hostage crisis in Beslan, Russia. 
The terrorists had released her mother and younger sister earlier. 
(NTV - 06/09/04; Anadolu Agency - 05/09/04)
